-- Former Greek PM Simitis Urges Coalition Government, Skai TV Says
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2012-06-18T10:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-18/former-greek-pm-simitis-urges-coalition-government-skai-tv-says.html
Former Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis said  New Democracy , Pasok and Democratic Left are
obligated to form a stable and effective coalition government,
 Skai TV  reported, without saying where it got the information.  Simitis, the former head of the socialist Pasok party and
prime minister of Greece from 1996 to 2004, said the three
parties were pro-Europe and should work together to prevent an
exit from the single euro currency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in Athens at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
